  "title": "Vows on the Bridge of the Emendation",
  "summary": "On the bridge of the warship Emendation, on the eve of a battle with the Sith, Colonel Gren Delede and the Twi'lek pilot Twila Virda are married in a hasty ceremony. A newly assigned chaplain officiates, first probing whether the couple weds out of love or fear of dying, before accepting their sincerity. Gren names Twila to the bridge crew as witnesses and reveals he has just brevetted her to First Lieutenant, surprising her mid-ceremony. The two exchange heartfelt vows under the authority of the Corporate Sector Authority's charter, and Gren gives Twila his father's engraved whiskey flask in lieu of a ring. The chaplain pronounces them husband and wife, and the couple kisses, agreeing to postpone the honeymoon until after the coming fight.",
